description:

Even though the worst of the credit crunch is meant to be long gone, never has the need to earn a few extra pounds been more pressing. That s where eBay comes in, with over ?1,000 per second changing hands on eBay across the world, it s become a favoured shopping destination of many. For buyer s, it s a chance to snap up some great deals, and save valuable pounds on items against the high-street price and a treasure trove of items you simply wouldn t be able to get anywhere else. 

For sellers, there is no other place that can offer you wares to over 230 million people through one website and many have gone on to base successful businesses around the eBay service. Saying this, it s not as simple as it seems. Knowing if that bargain is as good as it looks, trying to figure out if you re being scammed and knowing how to make your products more appealing are just some of the considerations we need to make. This guide is jam-packed with secrets of successful buying and selling, cons as well as pros, meaning you might just be able to do your bank balance the world of good!
